status_message:
Donald J. Trump: "I did not support the war in Iraq." 

FALSE. 

Trump was on the record as supportive of the Iraq War as early as a month before Congress voted to authorize military force in Iraq and even soon after the invasion. status_message:
Smugglers had promised 33-year-old Sabeel that $400 would buy him passage to Europe on a cargo ship or a fishing trawler. The reality: A 20-foot-long inflatable dinghy, powered by an outboard motor.

Built for 25 people, 133 were squeezed in. An hour after one of the smugglers took the migrants out to sea, he left the vessel — taking a fast boat back to land.

"See those stars," he told the migrants, pointing upward before he left. "They mean north. Follow them."

Suddenly ocean and sky were the same color: Black.

This is the story of one desperate day at sea – and the rescue mission that saved Sabeel and thousands of others: http://cnn.it/2bEyvcO
link_name: "These crossings are nothing but fatal"

Are you addicted to your phone? CNN is looking for three volunteers to be featured in an upcoming CNN.com project about how mobile devices are changing our lives.

Do you live much of your social life – texts, Facebook, Web surfing, photo-sharing – through your phone? To participate in the project, you would keep track of all your phone usage for an entire week: every text, email, Facebook post, Google search, "Angry Birds" level, and so on. The idea is to demonstrate how much of our lives we live and share through our phones.

If you're interested, please email us at CNN.features.sources@gmail.com and tell us briefly about yourself and your phone usage habits. Someone from CNN may be in touch with you. Thanks!

status_message:
Smugglers had promised 33-year-old Sabeel that $400 would buy him passage to Europe on a cargo ship or a fishing trawler. The reality: A 20-foot-long inflatable dinghy, powered by an outboard motor.

Built for 25 people, 133 were squeezed in. An hour after one of the smugglers took the migrants out to sea, he left the vessel — taking a fast boat back to land.

"See those stars," he told the migrants, pointing upward before he left. "They mean north. Follow them."

Suddenly ocean and sky were the same color: Black.

This is the story of one desperate day at sea – and the rescue mission that saved Sabeel and thousands of others: http://cnn.it/2bEyvcO
link_name: "These crossings are nothing but fatal"

Are you addicted to your phone? CNN is looking for three volunteers to be featured in an upcoming CNN.com project about how mobile devices are changing our lives.

Do you live much of your social life – texts, Facebook, Web surfing, photo-sharing – through your phone? To participate in the project, you would keep track of all your phone usage for an entire week: every text, email, Facebook post, Google search, "Angry Birds" level, and so on. The results would be featured on CNN.com, and we might ask to publish some of the data (texts, photos, etc.), with your permission. The idea is to demonstrate how much of our lives we live and share through our phones.

If you're interested, please email us at CNN.features.sources@gmail.com and tell us briefly about yourself and your phone usage habits. Someone from CNN may be in touch with you. Thanks!
